 harry could smell salt and hear rushing waves a light chilly breeze ruffled his hair as he looked out at moonlit sea and sky he was standing upon a high outcrop of dark rock water foaming and churning below him he glanced over his shoulder a towering cliff stood behind them a sheer drop black and faceless a few large chunks of rock such as the one upon which harry and dumbledore were standing looked as though they had broken away from the cliff face at some point in the past it was a bleak harsh view the sea and the rock unrelieved by any tree or sweep of grass or sand 
 
